  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis was that education of rehabilitation officers who were responsible for
      rehabilitation back to work for sick-listed individuals in screening for mental disorders and
      psychiatric topics would increase the rate of return to work and reduce the number of
      sicklisted days
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
